# Surge RULE-SET (REJECT / BLOCKLIST)
# Target Policy: REJECT
# Purpose:
# - Block high-value ads/trackers/malware/telemetry endpoints
# - Keep list small to reduce false positives
#
# Recommended order in Surge [Rule]:
#   RULE-SET,https://jovanykoch.github.io/loon/rules/allow.list,DIRECT
#   RULE-SET,https://jovanykoch.github.io/loon/rules/reject.list,REJECT
#   RULE-SET,https://jovanykoch.github.io/loon/rules/apple.list,DIRECT
#   RULE-SET,https://jovanykoch.github.io/loon/rules/github.list,Proxy
#   RULE-SET,https://jovanykoch.github.io/loon/rules/proxy.list,Proxy
#   RULE-SET,https://jovanykoch.github.io/loon/rules/china.list,DIRECT
#   GEOIP,CN,DIRECT
#   FINAL,Proxy
#
# Notes:
# - Prefer DOMAIN-SUFFIX for vendor tracking domains.
# - Avoid overly broad rules that break apps.

# -----------------------
# Ads / tracking / analytics (high-value)
# -----------------------
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,doubleclick.net
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,googleads.g.doubleclick.net
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,googlesyndication.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,googletagmanager.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,googletagservices.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,adservice.google.com

DOMAIN-SUFFIX,scorecardresearch.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,quantserve.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,crashlytics.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,appsflyer.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,adjust.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,branch.io
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,segment.io
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,mixpanel.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,amplitude.com

# Facebook / Meta tracking
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,facebook-analytics.com
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,connect.facebook.net

# Microsoft telemetry / analytics (minimal)
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,appcenter.ms

# -----------------------
# Crypto mining / unwanted
# -----------------------
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,coinhive.com